The `atob` function is used to decode a Base64 encoded string.

Please note that Base64 encoding will increase the size of your string by approximately 33%, so it's not a compression method, but it's a good way to encode data for sharing in URLs because Base64 characters are safe to use in URLs.

Also, Base64 encoding is not secure, so it's not suitable for sensitive data. If you need to share sensitive data, consider using more secure methods like JSON Web Token (JWT) or other encryption methods.

